snippet.textDisplay: "Praise to he creator" is wrong. The beloved could be haqiqi (divine) or majazi (of this world/human). This ambiguity in sufi performances is common, lovable and makes this genre attract wider audiences. So the more appropriate and inclusive translation of Afreen is "Praise the beloved's creator".  Furthermore, Momina took the performance to whole new level despite pairing up with Rahat.  Giving her fewer lines would mean she was there for cosmetic not artistic reasons.
